President Trump delivered remarks at the Conservative Political Action Conference in which he discussed a range of topics, including tax cuts, immigration, and school safety. He emphasized the need for stronger borders and stricter immigration policies, and called for the construction of a border wall. He also advocated for arming teachers and other school staff members as a means of improving school safety. Additionally, Trump spoke about his administration's efforts to reduce crime and increase prosecutions of violent offenders. He concluded by expressing his optimism for the future and urging his audience to continue supporting Republican candidates in the upcoming elections.